{"paragraphs":[{"cues":[{"time":0,"text":"I'd like to talk a little bit this morning"},{"time":2000,"text":"about what happens if we move from design"},{"time":5000,"text":"to design thinking."},{"time":8000,"text":"Now this rather old photo up there"},{"time":10000,"text":"is actually the first project I was ever hired to do,"},{"time":13000,"text":"something like 25 years ago."},{"time":15000,"text":"It's a woodworking machine, or at least a piece of one,"},{"time":17000,"text":"and my task was to"},{"time":19000,"text":"make this thing a little bit more modern,"},{"time":21000,"text":"a little bit easier to use."},{"time":23000,"text":"I thought, at the time, I did a pretty good job."},{"time":26000,"text":"Unfortunately, not very long afterwards"},{"time":28000,"text":"the company went out of business."}]},{"cues":[{"time":31000,"text":"This is the second project that I did. It's a fax machine."},{"time":34000,"text":"I put an attractive shell around some new technology."},{"time":37000,"text":"Again, 18 months later,"},{"time":39000,"text":"the product was obsolete."},{"time":41000,"text":"And now, of course, the whole technology is obsolete."},{"time":46000,"text":"Now, I'm a fairly slow learner,"},{"time":48000,"text":"but eventually it occurred to me that"},{"time":50000,"text":"maybe what passed for design"},{"time":52000,"text":"wasn't all that important --"},{"time":54000,"text":"making things more attractive,"},{"time":56000,"text":"making them a bit easier to use,"},{"time":58000,"text":"making them more marketable."},{"time":61000,"text":"By focusing on a design,"},{"time":63000,"text":"maybe just a single product,"},{"time":65000,"text":"I was being incremental"},{"time":67000,"text":"and not having much of an impact."}]},{"cues":[{"time":71000,"text":"But I think this small view of design"},{"time":73000,"text":"is a relatively recent phenomenon,"},{"time":75000,"text":"and in fact really emerged"},{"time":77000,"text":"in the latter half of the 20th century"},{"time":79000,"text":"as design became a tool of consumerism."},{"time":83000,"text":"So when we talk about design today,"},{"time":85000,"text":"and particularly when we read about it in the popular press,"},{"time":88000,"text":"we're often talking about products like these."},{"time":90000,"text":"Amusing? Yes. Desirable? Maybe."},{"time":93000,"text":"Important? Not so very."}]},{"cues":[{"time":96000,"text":"But this wasn't always the way."},{"time":98000,"text":"And I'd like to suggest that if we take"},{"time":100000,"text":"a different view of design,"},{"time":102000,"text":"and focus less on the object"},{"time":105000,"text":"and more on design thinking as an approach,"},{"time":108000,"text":"that we actually might see the result in a bigger impact."},{"time":113000,"text":"Now this gentleman, Isambard Kingdom Brunel,"},{"time":115000,"text":"designed many great things in his career in the 19th century,"},{"time":119000,"text":"including the Clifton suspension bridge in Bristol"},{"time":123000,"text":"and the Thames tunnel at Rotherhithe."},{"time":125000,"text":"Both great designs and actually very innovative too."},{"time":130000,"text":"His greatest creation"},{"time":133000,"text":"runs actually right through here in Oxford."},{"time":135000,"text":"It's called the Great Western Railway."}]},{"cues":[{"time":138000,"text":"And as a kid I grew up very close to here,"},{"time":141000,"text":"and one of my favorite things to do"},{"time":143000,"text":"was to cycle along by the side of the railway"},{"time":146000,"text":"waiting for the great big express trains to roar past."},{"time":149000,"text":"You can see it represented here in J.M.W. Turner's painting,"},{"time":151000,"text":"\"Rain, Steam and Speed\"."},{"time":154000,"text":"Now, what Brunel said that he wanted to achieve for his passengers"},{"time":158000,"text":"was the experience of floating across the countryside."}]},{"cues":[{"time":163000,"text":"Now, this was back in the 19th century."},{"time":165000,"text":"And to do that meant creating the flattest gradients"},{"time":167000,"text":"that had ever yet been made,"},{"time":169000,"text":"which meant building long viaducts across river valleys --"},{"time":172000,"text":"this is actually the viaduct across the Thames at Maidenhead --"},{"time":176000,"text":"and long tunnels such as the one at Box, in Wiltshire."},{"time":182000,"text":"But he didn't stop there. He didn't stop"},{"time":184000,"text":"with just trying to design the best railway journey."},{"time":187000,"text":"He imagined an integrated transportation system"},{"time":191000,"text":"in which it would be possible for a passenger to embark"},{"time":194000,"text":"on a train in London"},{"time":197000,"text":"and disembark from a ship in New York."},{"time":200000,"text":"One journey from London to New York."},{"time":204000,"text":"This is the S.S. Great Western that he built"},{"time":206000,"text":"to take care of the second half of that journey."}]},{"cues":[{"time":210000,"text":"Now, Brunel was working 100 years before"},{"time":212000,"text":"the emergence of the design profession,"},{"time":215000,"text":"but I think he was using design thinking"},{"time":218000,"text":"to solve problems and to create world-changing innovations."},{"time":223000,"text":"Now, design thinking begins with what Roger Martin,"},{"time":225000,"text":"the business school professor at the University of Toronto,"},{"time":228000,"text":"calls integrative thinking."},{"time":230000,"text":"And that's the ability to exploit opposing ideas"},{"time":233000,"text":"and opposing constraints"},{"time":235000,"text":"to create new solutions."},{"time":237000,"text":"In the case of design, that means"},{"time":240000,"text":"balancing desirability, what humans need,"},{"time":244000,"text":"with technical feasibility,"},{"time":246000,"text":"and economic viability."},{"time":249000,"text":"With innovations like the Great Western,"},{"time":251000,"text":"we can stretch that balance to the absolute limit."}]},{"cues":[{"time":255000,"text":"So somehow, we went from this to this."},{"time":262000,"text":"Systems thinkers who were reinventing the world,"},{"time":265000,"text":"to a priesthood of folks in black turtlenecks and designer glasses"},{"time":270000,"text":"working on small things."},{"time":272000,"text":"As our industrial society matured,"},{"time":276000,"text":"so design became a profession"},{"time":278000,"text":"and it focused on an ever smaller canvas"},{"time":281000,"text":"until it came to stand for aesthetics,"},{"time":283000,"text":"image and fashion."},{"time":285000,"text":"Now I'm not trying to throw stones here."},{"time":288000,"text":"I'm a fully paid-up member of that priesthood,"},{"time":290000,"text":"and somewhere in here I have my designer glasses."},{"time":292000,"text":"There we go."},{"time":295000,"text":"But I do think that perhaps design"},{"time":297000,"text":"is getting big again."},{"time":299000,"text":"And that's happening through"},{"time":302000,"text":"the application of design thinking"},{"time":304000,"text":"to new kinds of problems --"},{"time":306000,"text":"to global warming, to education,"},{"time":308000,"text":"healthcare, security, clean water, whatever."}]},{"cues":[{"time":312000,"text":"And as we see this reemergence of design thinking"},{"time":315000,"text":"and we see it beginning to tackle new kinds of problems,"},{"time":318000,"text":"there are some basic ideas that I think we can observe that are useful."},{"time":321000,"text":"And I'd like to talk about some of those"},{"time":323000,"text":"just for the next few minutes."},{"time":325000,"text":"The first of those is that design is"},{"time":327000,"text":"human-centered."},{"time":330000,"text":"It may integrate technology and economics,"},{"time":332000,"text":"but it starts with what humans need, or might need."},{"time":336000,"text":"What makes life easier, more enjoyable?"},{"time":338000,"text":"What makes technology useful and usable?"},{"time":342000,"text":"But that is more than simply good ergonomics,"},{"time":345000,"text":"putting the buttons in the right place."},{"time":348000,"text":"It's often about understanding culture and context"},{"time":351000,"text":"before we even know where to start to have ideas."}]},{"cues":[{"time":354000,"text":"So when a team was working on a new vision screening program in India,"},{"time":358000,"text":"they wanted to understand what the aspirations"},{"time":360000,"text":"and motivations were of these school children"},{"time":363000,"text":"to understand how they might play a role"},{"time":365000,"text":"in screening their parents."},{"time":370000,"text":"Conversion Sound has developed a high quality,"},{"time":372000,"text":"ultra-low-cost digital hearing aid"},{"time":375000,"text":"for the developing world."},{"time":377000,"text":"Now, in the West we rely on highly trained technicians"},{"time":381000,"text":"to fit these hearing aids."},{"time":383000,"text":"In places like India, those technicians simply don't exist."},{"time":387000,"text":"So it took a team working in India"},{"time":389000,"text":"with patients and community health workers"},{"time":391000,"text":"to understand how a PDA"},{"time":393000,"text":"and an application on a PDA"},{"time":395000,"text":"might replace those technicians"},{"time":397000,"text":"in a fitting and diagnostic service."}]},{"cues":[{"time":400000,"text":"Instead of starting with technology,"},{"time":402000,"text":"the team started with people and culture."},{"time":405000,"text":"So if human need is the place to start,"},{"time":408000,"text":"then design thinking rapidly moves on to"},{"time":410000,"text":"learning by making."},{"time":412000,"text":"Instead of thinking about what to build,"},{"time":415000,"text":"building in order to think."},{"time":418000,"text":"Now, prototypes speed up the process of innovation,"},{"time":421000,"text":"because it is only when we put our ideas out into the world"},{"time":424000,"text":"that we really start to understand their strengths and weaknesses."},{"time":427000,"text":"And the faster we do that,"},{"time":429000,"text":"the faster our ideas evolve."}]},{"cues":[{"time":432000,"text":"Now, much has been said and written about"},{"time":434000,"text":"the Aravind Eye Institute in Madurai, India."},{"time":437000,"text":"They do an incredible job of serving very poor patients"},{"time":441000,"text":"by taking the revenues from those who can afford to pay"},{"time":443000,"text":"to cross-subsidize those who cannot."},{"time":447000,"text":"Now, they are very efficient,"},{"time":450000,"text":"but they are also very innovative."},{"time":453000,"text":"When I visited them a few years ago,"},{"time":456000,"text":"what really impressed me was their willingness"},{"time":458000,"text":"to prototype their ideas very early."}]},{"cues":[{"time":460000,"text":"This is the manufacturing facility"},{"time":462000,"text":"for one of their biggest cost breakthroughs."},{"time":464000,"text":"They make their own intraocular lenses."},{"time":467000,"text":"These are the lenses that replace those"},{"time":469000,"text":"that are damaged by cataracts."},{"time":471000,"text":"And I think it's partly their prototyping mentality"},{"time":475000,"text":"that really allowed them to achieve the breakthrough."},{"time":477000,"text":"Because they brought the cost down"},{"time":479000,"text":"from $200 a pair,"},{"time":480000,"text":"down to just $4 a pair."},{"time":485000,"text":"Partly they did this by instead of building"},{"time":487000,"text":"a fancy new factory,"},{"time":489000,"text":"they used the basement of one of their hospitals."},{"time":493000,"text":"And instead of installing the large-scale machines"},{"time":496000,"text":"used by western producers,"},{"time":498000,"text":"they used low-cost CAD/CAM prototyping technology."},{"time":502000,"text":"They are now the biggest manufacturer of these lenses in the developing world"},{"time":506000,"text":"and have recently moved into a custom factory."}]},{"cues":[{"time":510000,"text":"So if human need is the place to start,"},{"time":512000,"text":"and prototyping, a vehicle for progress,"},{"time":514000,"text":"then there are also some questions to ask about the destination."},{"time":518000,"text":"Instead of seeing its primary objective as consumption,"},{"time":523000,"text":"design thinking is beginning to explore the potential of participation --"},{"time":526000,"text":"the shift from a passive relationship"},{"time":529000,"text":"between consumer and producer"},{"time":531000,"text":"to the active engagement of everyone"},{"time":533000,"text":"in experiences that are meaningful,"},{"time":535000,"text":"productive and profitable."}]},{"cues":[{"time":539000,"text":"So I'd like to take the idea that Rory Sutherland talked about,"},{"time":542000,"text":"this notion that intangible things are worth perhaps more than physical things,"},{"time":545000,"text":"and take that a little bit further and say that"},{"time":547000,"text":"I think the design of participatory systems,"},{"time":550000,"text":"in which many more forms of value"},{"time":553000,"text":"beyond simply cash"},{"time":555000,"text":"are both created and measured,"},{"time":558000,"text":"is going to be the major theme, not only for design,"},{"time":561000,"text":"but also for our economy as we go forward."}]},{"cues":[{"time":565000,"text":"So William Beveridge, when he wrote the first of his famous reports in 1942,"},{"time":569000,"text":"created what became Britain's welfare state"},{"time":573000,"text":"in which he hoped that every citizen"},{"time":576000,"text":"would be an active participant"},{"time":578000,"text":"in their own social well-being."},{"time":580000,"text":"By the time he wrote his third report,"},{"time":583000,"text":"he confessed that he had failed"},{"time":585000,"text":"and instead had created a society of welfare consumers."}]},{"cues":[{"time":591000,"text":"Hilary Cottam, Charlie Leadbeater,"},{"time":593000,"text":"and Hugo Manassei of Participle"},{"time":595000,"text":"have taken this idea of participation,"},{"time":598000,"text":"and in their manifesto entitled Beveridge 4.0,"},{"time":601000,"text":"they are suggesting a framework"},{"time":603000,"text":"for reinventing the welfare state."},{"time":606000,"text":"So in one of their projects called Southwark Circle,"},{"time":608000,"text":"they worked with residents in Southwark, South London"},{"time":611000,"text":"and a small team of designers"},{"time":613000,"text":"to develop a new membership organization"},{"time":617000,"text":"to help the elderly with household tasks."},{"time":620000,"text":"Designs were refined and developed"},{"time":622000,"text":"with 150 older people and their families"},{"time":625000,"text":"before the service was launched earlier this year."}]},{"cues":[{"time":630000,"text":"We can take this idea of participation"},{"time":634000,"text":"perhaps to its logical conclusion"},{"time":636000,"text":"and say that design may have its greatest impact"},{"time":638000,"text":"when it's taken out of the hands of designers"},{"time":641000,"text":"and put into the hands of everyone."},{"time":644000,"text":"Nurses and practitioners at U.S. healthcare system"},{"time":647000,"text":"Kaiser Permanente"},{"time":649000,"text":"study the topic of improving the patient experience,"},{"time":654000,"text":"and particularly focused on the way that they exchange knowledge"},{"time":659000,"text":"and change shift."},{"time":662000,"text":"Through a program of observational research,"},{"time":664000,"text":"brainstorming new solutions and rapid prototyping,"},{"time":667000,"text":"they've developed a completely new way to change shift."}]},{"cues":[{"time":670000,"text":"They went from retreating to the nurse's station"},{"time":674000,"text":"to discuss the various states and needs of patients,"},{"time":676000,"text":"to developing a system that happened on the ward"},{"time":679000,"text":"in front of patients, using a simple software tool."},{"time":682000,"text":"By doing this they brought the time that they were away from patients"},{"time":684000,"text":"down from 40 minutes to 12 minutes, on average."},{"time":688000,"text":"They increased patient confidence and nurse happiness."},{"time":692000,"text":"When you multiply that by all the nurses"},{"time":694000,"text":"in all the wards in 40 hospitals in the system,"},{"time":697000,"text":"it resulted, actually, in a pretty big impact."}]},{"cues":[{"time":699000,"text":"And this is just one of thousands"},{"time":701000,"text":"of opportunities in healthcare alone."},{"time":707000,"text":"So these are just some of the kind of basic ideas"},{"time":710000,"text":"around design thinking"},{"time":712000,"text":"and some of the new kinds of projects"},{"time":714000,"text":"that they're being applied to."},{"time":717000,"text":"But I'd like to go back to Brunel here,"},{"time":719000,"text":"and suggest a connection that might explain why this is happening now,"},{"time":723000,"text":"and maybe why design thinking is a useful tool."},{"time":728000,"text":"And that connection is change."},{"time":731000,"text":"In times of change we need"},{"time":733000,"text":"new alternatives, new ideas."}]},{"cues":[{"time":737000,"text":"Now, Brunel worked at the height of the Industrial Revolution,"},{"time":739000,"text":"when all of life and our economy"},{"time":741000,"text":"was being reinvented."},{"time":743000,"text":"Now the industrial systems of Brunel's time have run their course,"},{"time":747000,"text":"and indeed they are part of the problem today."},{"time":749000,"text":"But, again, we are in the midst of massive change."},{"time":753000,"text":"And that change is forcing us to question"},{"time":756000,"text":"quite fundamental aspects of our society --"},{"time":758000,"text":"how we keep ourselves healthy, how we govern ourselves,"},{"time":761000,"text":"how we educate ourselves, how we keep ourselves secure."},{"time":765000,"text":"And in these times of change, we need these new choices"},{"time":768000,"text":"because our existing solutions are simply becoming obsolete."}]},{"cues":[{"time":773000,"text":"So why design thinking?"},{"time":775000,"text":"Because it gives us a new way of tackling problems."},{"time":778000,"text":"Instead of defaulting to our normal convergent approach"},{"time":783000,"text":"where we make the best choice out of available alternatives,"},{"time":787000,"text":"it encourages us to take a divergent approach,"},{"time":790000,"text":"to explore new alternatives, new solutions,"},{"time":792000,"text":"new ideas that have not existed before."},{"time":796000,"text":"But before we go through that process of divergence,"},{"time":798000,"text":"there is actually quite an important first step."},{"time":801000,"text":"And that is, what is the question that we're trying to answer?"},{"time":804000,"text":"What's the design brief?"},{"time":806000,"text":"Now Brunel may have asked a question like this,"},{"time":808000,"text":"\"How do I take a train from London to New York?\""},{"time":812000,"text":"But what are the kinds of questions that we might ask today?"}]},{"cues":[{"time":816000,"text":"So these are some that we've been asked to think about recently."},{"time":822000,"text":"And one in particular, is one that we're working on with the Acumen Fund,"},{"time":825000,"text":"in a project that's been funded by the Bill and Melinda Gates Foundation."},{"time":829000,"text":"How might we improve access to safe drinking water"},{"time":832000,"text":"for the world's poorest people,"},{"time":834000,"text":"and at the same time stimulate innovation"},{"time":836000,"text":"amongst local water providers?"}]},{"cues":[{"time":840000,"text":"So instead of having a bunch of American designers"},{"time":842000,"text":"come up with new ideas that may or may not have been appropriate,"},{"time":845000,"text":"we took a sort of more open, collaborative and participative approach."},{"time":849000,"text":"We teamed designers and investment experts up with"},{"time":852000,"text":"11 water organizations across India."},{"time":855000,"text":"And through workshops they developed"},{"time":857000,"text":"innovative new products, services, and business models."}]},{"cues":[{"time":860000,"text":"We hosted a competition"},{"time":862000,"text":"and then funded five of those organizations"},{"time":864000,"text":"to develop their ideas."},{"time":866000,"text":"So they developed and iterated these ideas."},{"time":868000,"text":"And then IDEO and Acumen spent several weeks working with them"},{"time":871000,"text":"to help design new social marketing campaigns,"},{"time":876000,"text":"community outreach strategies, business models,"},{"time":879000,"text":"new water vessels for storing water"},{"time":881000,"text":"and carts for delivering water."},{"time":884000,"text":"Some of those ideas are just getting launched into the market."},{"time":886000,"text":"And the same process is just getting underway"},{"time":888000,"text":"with NGOs in East Africa."}]},{"cues":[{"time":891000,"text":"So for me, this project shows"},{"time":894000,"text":"kind of how far we can go from"},{"time":896000,"text":"some of those sort of small things"},{"time":898000,"text":"that I was working on"},{"time":900000,"text":"at the beginning of my career."},{"time":902000,"text":"That by focusing on the needs of humans"},{"time":906000,"text":"and by using prototypes"},{"time":908000,"text":"to move ideas along quickly,"},{"time":910000,"text":"by getting the process out of the hands of designers,"},{"time":913000,"text":"and by getting the active participation of the community,"},{"time":916000,"text":"we can tackle bigger and more interesting questions."},{"time":919000,"text":"And just like Brunel, by focusing on systems,"},{"time":922000,"text":"we can have a bigger impact."},{"time":925000,"text":"So that's one thing that we've been working on."}]},{"cues":[{"time":928000,"text":"I'm actually really quite interested, and perhaps more interested"},{"time":931000,"text":"to know what this community thinks we could work on."},{"time":935000,"text":"What kinds of questions do we think"},{"time":938000,"text":"design thinking could be used to tackle?"},{"time":941000,"text":"And if you've got any ideas"},{"time":943000,"text":"then feel free, you can post them to Twitter."},{"time":945000,"text":"There is a hash tag there that you can use, #CBDQ."},{"time":948000,"text":"And the list looked something like this a little while ago."},{"time":951000,"text":"And of course you can search to find the questions that you're interested in"},{"time":955000,"text":"by using the same hash code."}]},{"cues":[{"time":957000,"text":"So I'd like to believe that design thinking"},{"time":961000,"text":"actually can make a difference,"},{"time":963000,"text":"that it can help create new ideas"},{"time":965000,"text":"and new innovations,"},{"time":967000,"text":"beyond the latest High Street products."},{"time":969000,"text":"To do that I think we have to take a more expansive view of design,"},{"time":973000,"text":"more like Brunel, less a domain of a professional priesthood."},{"time":979000,"text":"And the first step is to start asking the right questions."},{"time":982000,"text":"Thank you very much."},{"time":984000,"text":"(Applause)"}]}]}